    <h3>The Calcium Paradox</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Young women in Florida with osteopenia despite calcium supplements</li>
        <li>Calcium added to milk, orange juice, everything</li>
        <li>Still have weak bones – why?</li>
        <li>Missing cofactors: D3 and K2</li>
        <li>Calcium goes to arteries instead of bones</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How Calcium Becomes Deadly</h3>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Without D3:</strong> Poor absorption from gut</li>
        <li><strong>Without K2:</strong> Calcium deposits in arteries</li>
        <li><strong>Result:</strong> Arterial calcification + weak bones</li>
        <li><strong>Irony:</strong> Taking calcium causes what you're trying to prevent</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="warning-box">
